This privacy policy ("Privacy Policy") applies to the Scour Websites (Scour.ai and any such as ), products, and services, and describes how personal information is collected, used, disclosed, and protected by For convenience, the Scour Websites and our services are collectively referred to as the "Service". The exception to this is if you are part of an organization that has a separate written agreement with Scour covering the use of our Service in which case any terms in that agreement describing how Scour handles your personal information take Scour Service and Customer Services Data Customers and registered users of the Service ("Customers") use the Service to connect Customer applications and services ("Customer Services") to their users accounts ("End-User Accounts") and transfer data ("Customer Services Data") between the Service and Customer Services Data may include, without limitation, personal data and information about the identity of Customer users, such as email addresses, names, phone numbers, postal addresses, IP addresses, age, and actions they take while using Customer In addition to reviewing this Privacy Policy, please refer to our Customers policies for information regarding their collection, use, and disclosure of your personal Our use of Customer Services Data provided by our Customers in connection with our Service is subject to the written agreement between Scour and the If you are using Scour as a , please contact us for our Data Processing Agreement to accept it if applicable Personal Information Collected We collect information from you in various ways when you use our Service, including Customer Services Data described We may also supplement this information with information from other As used in this Privacy Policy, the term personal information means information that specifically identifies an individual (such as, but not limited to, a name, email address, or IP address), and demographic and other information when directly or indirectly linked to information that can identify an Information you give us The following are the specific types of information you give to We collect information you give us on our Service and when you register for and use our Registration information ‚Äî When you register to use our service, we may collect your name, email address, phone number, postal address, and IP You may log into your Scour account to access our services using functionality such as via your Google or GitHub This feature uses those services application programming interfaces (API) to authenticate your identity and automatically share certain personal information with us like your name and We use similar methods to connect your cloud service connected accounts ‚Äî Similar to Accounts, you may choose to connect accounts of your own to the This is treated the same as Please refer to our Data Processing Agreement for more information on how we handle this Payment and Transaction Information ‚Äî If you choose to use a paid Scour account or service, our vendor, Stripe, directly collects your credit card information and billing We never receive this Stripe commits to complying with the Payment Card Industry Data Security Standard (PCI-DSS) and using Stripe may use your Payment Information in accordance with its own Privacy Policy here: https: stripe.com us privacy . Scour also receives transaction information on details of your purchase and billing details such as the last four digits of a credit card number and billing Feedback and correspondence ‚Äî Information you provide when you respond to surveys, report a problem with the Service, receive customer support, let us know how you use the Service, or otherwise correspond with Marketing information ‚Äî Your preferences for receiving marketing communications and details on how you interact with this option to choose your Information automatically collected We gather certain information automatically and store it in log This information includes internet protocol (IP) addresses, browser type, internet service provider (ISP), referring exit pages, operating system, date time stamp, links clicked on, search terms, and other We collect this information in server logs, and by using Cookies and similar tracking technologies to analyze trends, administer the website, track users movements around the website, gather demographic information about our user base as a whole, and deliver Sco

Technical Articles Presentations About About DTP Events Contact Thermoelectric Applications DTP technology enables new uses for thermoelectrics Compared to conventional thermoelectric (TE) material, DTP enables cooling to a larger temperature difference and with a higher Thanks to this combination of features, you can operate at a higher coefficient of performance (COP) and also provide more heat pumping These benefits make DTP a superior thermal management choice for many applications and industries‚Äîincluding automotive, cold chain logistics, medical, electrical propulsion, smart buildings and Automotive With its superior cooling capacity, wide temperature differential and high COP, our DTP technology delivers thermal management improvements to both internal combustion and electric In vehicles with internal combustion engines (ICE), DTP thermoelectric devices can be incorporated as a into conventional vapor compression HVAC The resulting hybrid HVAC systems can reach new levels of efficiency and offer more cooling capacity than conventional automotive HVAC systems, creating opportunities to downsize heating and cooling subsystems without sacrificing passenger In electric vehicles (EV), a DTP thermoelectric system can provide a holistic solution to all the vehicle s thermal management needs‚Äîfrom efficient cooling and heating of passenger cabins to battery thermal management solutions that improve the range and longevity of automotive Applications Vehicle cabin cooling and heating in both ICE and EV EV battery thermal management Exhaust heat recovery systems in ICE vehicles Hydrogen fuel cell thermal management Medical DTP is ideal for many applications in the medical industry that require precise thermal management‚Äîfrom cryosurgery to Due to its higher temperature differential, COP and efficiency, it also lends itself well to therapeutic techniques requiring heating or cooling, eliminating the need for imprecise and cumbersome ice packs or heating Applications Cryosurgery Cardiac cryoablation Renal denervation Lab automation Polymerase chain reaction (PCR) Microfluidic pumps and valves Cold Chain Logistics Achieving proper temperatures for vaccine transportation and delivery can be a challenging task using conventional Oftentimes, to increase the temperature difference to be able to hit ¬∞C, these technologies must be utilized alongside cascade DTP overcomes these issues by operating at a higher efficiency and COP compared to conventional It also utilizes less TE material in the process, reducing the cost and complexity of the cold chain management In addition, DTP doesn‚Äôt require dry ice, which isn‚Äôt always plentiful in the regions a vaccine is traveling Compared to Stirling engines, you can also easily scale this technology, enabling smaller carriers to transport vaccines to or inaccessible Applications Cold chain storage Vaccine transportation and delivery Thermal packaging Pharmaceuticals Electric Propulsion Beyond passenger vehicles, the benefits of DTP extend to any vehicle that utilizes electric propulsion, including unmanned aerial vehicles (UAV) and underwater remotely operated vehicles (ROV). Create innovative hardware + software projects with Use Your Creativity to Build Projects That Benefit the World! (Nov, - Jan, ) Register Now! What is ? is a program run by , a (c)(3) organization where we provide passionate students with an opportunity to learn the ropes of computer science engineering by enabling them to start their own projects while mentoring them on their We aim to host an event that allows students to express their creativity and eliminate the social and economic obstacles surrounding programming and There will be prizes , free swag , and awesome tech speakers from the industry! The event will run from November , - January , Participants who are unable to financially fund their projects have the opportunity to apply for a grant, where they can receive the necessary funding for hardware + software components for their At , we strive to solve most pressing issues in our local This year, will focus on tackling two Community During the pandemic, local communities and groups are more vulnerable than How can we help those around us cope together when we are isolated? How can we provide easy access to the updates in the healthcare system? Innovate a hardware + software project that benefits and supports your local community during the pandemic CyberSecurity Billions of accounts are hacked each year due to the lack of cybersecurity in our everyday How can we support our local communities by securing our school, business and recreational networks? How can we increase our online cybersecurity presence through hardware and software? Innovate a hardware + software project that makes the a safer place Process How It Works 1) Register Apply Fill out the registration or grant On the grant form, You will answer questions about your project and your interests in Once you ve completed the written application on the grant form, we will schedule an interview to get to know you better! 2) Create Construct During this phase, you may start creating your hardware + software project You can take inspiration from our two pathaways: the cybersecurity track and the local community However, you may choose to create a project outside of these two fields 3) Analyze Revise Once you have completed the first drafts of your projects, mentors will be available to assist and support you on your journey This is the phase where you can ask questions, explore your project vision, prepare for the presentation, and improve your 4) Present Publish! Publish and present your project to our team and a panel of Demonstrate your innovation s functionalities and your design process The panel will judge and provide constructive feedback about your Through the presentation, you will have a chance to win hardware prizes Prizes Swag, Tech, and More! Overall Grand Prize Best Community Hack Best CyberSecurity Hack Best Beginner Hack Hardware Hack Place Best Hack Free + Stickers for all And Many More to Be Announced! Distributed Performance Management of Service Meshes | Layer5 Projects Meshery Landscape Service Mesh Performance Distributed Performance Management Service Mesh Interface Conformance Image Hub: Envoy Filters with WebAssembly Community Join Partners Programs Learn Books Events Workshops Learn Layer5 Blog News Run Meshery Distributed Performance Management of Service Meshes Purpose and Overview Distributed load testing offers insight into system behaviors that arguably more accurately represent real world behaviors of services under load as that load comes from any number of Project Aim The main aim of this project is to enhance the current load generation and analysis technique of Nighthawk to include distributed load testing which may ultimately benefit the meshery to directly adopt the distributed load Project Goals Identifying the of Working with the nighthawk team to successfully enable distributed load generation in Integrating the Nighthawk into the Meshery server and improving the load handling for Nighthawk using the Handling of the report and displaying mechanisms at the Testing & Debugging the Load Generator & finishing the implementation on Need for the Project Currently, Meshery which is a mesh management plane which can operate & adapt to various different service meshes only supports a single way load Understanding the need to support a variety of performance testing scenarios, Meshery has been equipped with a load generator interface as a point of extensibility to support the use of different load generators (see Meshery Extensibility documentation). Meshery Load Generation currently has been equipped with support for both wrk2 and fortio, neither of which support distributed load Why NightHawk Nighthawk is a versatile HTTP load testing tool built out of a need to drill HTTP services with a constant request It can be used both as a utility and a Contributors This project is being developed by Kush Trivedi as a Google Summer of Code project with the CNCF and in collaboration with Layer5 and Here is the design document for invoking distributed load generation & performance benchmarking using Participate in the CNCF Service Mesh Working Group Jump into the #performance channel to learn more about this Other Projects Distributed Performance Management of Service Meshes Image Hub: Envoy Filters using WebAssembly and Rust Meshery Service Mesh Interface Conformance Service Mesh Landscape Service Mesh Performance Mailing List Stay meshy and subscribe account_box mail Resources Service Mesh Comparison Service Mesh Tools Service Mesh Books Service Mesh Workshops Community Blog Events Partners Internships GSoC GSoD CommunityBridge Company News Brand Careers Contact Projects Meshery Service Mesh Landscape Service Mesh Interface Service Mesh Performance Language Get Involved! CyberDefenders is a training platform focused on the defensive side of cybersecurity, aiming to provide a place for blue teams to practice, validate the skills they have and acquire the ones they Our mission is to help security analysts improve their defensive skills through a set of blue team challenges offering an easy and quick way to provision , dedicated and disposable cloud labs needed to test and develop detection What is the difference between challenges and labs? Challenges are blue team CTF s meant to provide a way to practice blue team They come in different formats such as attack investigation (SIEM style), PCAP analysis, memory Each challenge has it s own scenario and list of Answering questions correctly requires going through an investigation scenario, analyzing data and extracting the right piece of Labs is the place where defenders can provision cloud environments to practice, validate and test stuff on their For example you can provision DetectionLabELK if you consider adopting MITRE ATT&CK framework and would like to develop detections for its You can use it to quickly run atomic tests, see what logs are being generated and compare it to your production Is it free? Challenges are Labs are To provision a lab, you will need to buy credits to accomodate the cost of running lab instances on the cloud since this lab is dedicated for The good news is that you will pay only for what you meaning, your credit balance will be utilized only for the uptime duration of any lab you provision on an hourly Each lab has a different cost based on the number of instances A lab with a single machine will cost less than a lab composed of four Each lab has its cost displayed on the lab information Who can access my labs? Only Those labs are dedicated and not shared with anybody When you provision a lab, your IP address will be automatically added to a whitelist on the firewall so that nobody else can see or access the What happens when I terminate a lab? Frequently Asked Questions ‚Äì PeerStorage Login Register Become a Host Home About Us Storage Listings List Your Space Blog FAQ Contact us Home About Us Storage Listings List Your Space Blog FAQ Contact us Login Register Become a Host Home Frequently Asked Questions Frequently Asked Questions We know you have some questions and hopefully we have the answers! Here are set of common questions our users have asked us in the If it does not answer your concerns then please contact us with any questions and we will be happy to address Renter Questions How are hosts verified by the service? Our service screens each and every host with the ‚Äúverified‚Äù stamp on the listing page to prove they are who they say they are and they are the owner of the All Storage hosts with the verified stamp on their listing are required to provide proof of identification such as driver‚Äôs license, passport photos, or other forms of Storage hosts also provide their phone number, email, address, and even a selfie We also ask our Renters to review the listing to verify all information about the listing is This will help provide a more trusted service for our Renters and help good Storage hosts with occupying their rental How do I know my items are safe? All verified Storage hosts have provided their drivers license or another form of identification, phone number, email, and We make it our due diligence to verify all Storage hosts are who they say they are so our rental customers feel safe using our PeerStorage also requires all entrances to storage spaces to be lockable, unless otherwise approved by the Whether this is by a physical locking mechanism such as a lock and key, digital lock, or padlock, the renter has the right to be in control of the key to the rented We take pride in providing the most secure service to our customers and it is our policy that all entrances to the space shall be secured at all times, unless previously specified by the Storage host and agreed upon by In terms of parking spaces and vehicle storage, the listed space may have no possible secured locking mechanism to the It is upon the owner of the vehicle to make sure the vehicle is How much does storage cost? The Renter will pay upfront for the service to the Storage host at a fraction of the cost of traditional The rental rate is based upon the size (sq. ) of the space making it competitive in any area across the PeerStorage lets Storage hosts choose their rental rates but suggest %-50% lower than traditional Rental rates are fixed for the duration of the reservation, meaning there will be no increased rental rates within the reservation period (move in date ‚Äì move out date). What is not allowed in storage? It‚Äôs your responsibility as a Renter to ensure that your items in storage will not cause any damage or harm to the space or space Restricted items include: Any hazardous or illegal items Guns and ammunition Fireworks Hazardous waste or chemicals Living or dead organisms Pesticides and toxins Drugs Flammable materials Stolen goods Perishable food items When placing a reservation, we recommend you disclose the items you will be storing with your Storage Host may further specify any other restricted items in their For additional items on what not to store, please see PeerStorage‚Äôs Terms & Conditions page . When and how often can I access my things? Access to your possessions depends on the ‚ÄúAccess times‚Äù displayed on the There are also daily, weekly, or monthly listing types where Renters can access their items multiple times during those Renters can always communicate with their Storage hosts through the platform messaging service in your dashboard in times of need to access possession‚Äôs. We ask that you give your host at least notice on when you need to access your How are payments handled? Payments are handled through our platform when you make a Renters may choose to pay with PayPal, debit or credit card, while cash payments are not Our service fees will be taken from each payment transaction paid by the Renter to the Storage Does the home owner have access to the rented storage space? Access control depends on the listing and agreement by the Storage host and Listings on PeerStorage are only meant for storage rental and are not intended for other The Renter has the right to request control of access to the storage Their may be certain instances where the Storage host needs access to the area, this should be mentioned to the Renter upon In case of any emergency the Storage host has the right to request access from the Renter if the Renter is in control of the key to the What if a host goes on vacation or isn‚Äôt home while I need to move out my stuff? The Storage host should use PeerStorage‚Äôs messaging system to communicate with the Renter on any unforeseen absences from their A Storage host must notify the Renter if they will be gone from their property for at least 7 days or over the period of the Renters move out If the Renter is denied access to their stuff

They are basically everywhere and there is this huge hype about ¬ªBut what on Earth are NFTs?!? ¬´ you may Well, let‚Äôs start at the beginning NFT stands for a token, which is a unit of data on the blockchain (you probably know what that is, right?), and each one of them can represent a unique digital item such as art, audio, video, video game items and other things that are considered creative So, as such NFTs are not interchangeable, which makes them different than all the other cryptocurrencies, because as a currency alone they are useless but they are very useful for other What reasons? Well, let‚Äôs look at digital art for A digital piece of art called ‚ÄúEverydays-The First ‚Äù created by Mike Winkelmann aka Beeple was sold for $69 million at an auction a couple of weeks $69 MILLION! Crazy right? Image: Beeple After all, it‚Äôs just a collage of 5,000 images right? Well, but then again, Mona Lisa is just a painting of a painfully woman with a weak smile and by some calculations, it‚Äôs supposedly worth million dollars! Is she really worth that kind of money? I‚Äôm going to leave that one up to you And that‚Äôs the thing art‚Äôs value can only be determined by the market and not by anyone‚Äôs personal opinion, which is exactly how digital artworks as If somebody is prepared to pay $69 million for a JPEG, so be It is the ultimate flex in the digital world, being the owner of a digital art worth millions of dollars through an Welcome to the Now that we went through NFTs , you should know that the NFT industry is booming and is hotter than Kim Kardashian in her Thousands of artists and businesses are selling their art and other forms of creative work through NFTs, and the best thing about it is, NFTs can be resold, most of them are rising up in value and you can also trade them with other members of the NFT community through different platforms and It‚Äôs kind of like trading Pokemon cards, but Once you are an owner of a digital piece of art, nobody can take it away from you because it is written on the digital ledger also known as the blockchain‚Ä¶that sounds familiar, right? If you know what I am talking about, then you also know that the blockchain cannot be erased and its data is here to stay üëëALL HAIL THE KINGüëë scooped up this Legendary LeBron James Moment from our Cosmic Series 1 set for $208,000‚ÄºÔ∏è This Moment is from our first Legendary set ever minted üíØ The top acquisition for any NBA Top Shot Moment ‚Ä¶ so Congrats on the nice pickup! üëë rFLMzbwXN7 ‚Äî NBA Top Shot (@nbatopshot) February , twitter: If you don‚Äôt know what I am talking about, you just might be living under a rock and in that case you might have to brush up on your Google skills because that‚Äôs a whole another ball game to go through and we will leave that one for another For now, you just need to know that NFT is all the rage at the moment, and if I were to make a guess, it just might be the future of all kinds of creative It is an opportunity for talented artists to be seen and be able to show their art to the No matter if you are an artist or a project creator, or if you are just looking to beef up your digital wallet, keep in mind, that there is a bright future for the NFT industry and we are very excited to be bringing the hottest news, artists, and projects directly to your screen, so hang around and fasten your seat belt, it‚Äôs going to be a moon ride! Steadfast Supported Living Holds two separate contracts with Washington One contract is with the Division of Developmental Administration (DDA). This is a Licensed Residential Services contract (LSR). Residents living in these homes qualify for DDA services and are found accommodations voluntarily by their legal guardians The other contract is with the Washington State Department of Children and Family Services (DCFS). This is a Behavioral Rehabilitation Services (BRS) Residents placed in BRS homes have extreme emotional and behavioral issues related to their history of abuse, neglect, trauma, and We dedicate each home location to either DDA or BRS residents‚Äìnot Up to five residents live in each home, and each resident has their own Each home is staffed 7 with staff rotations staff do not live Staff are trained to use models to provide the most effective Steadfast Supported Living Has chosen to provide homes for residents rather than a This makes it possible to provide highly structured services in an environment that promotes a home setting, making the transition back to family or foster care a more lateral How does Steadfast Supported Living Measure success? When people ask us this, they are typically looking for However, we measure success on an individual As with everything part of our program, we look at each person When measuring success, we reflect on the support and interventions, and we consider every small step along the way a success! How Are people placed in Steadfast Supported Living Programs and homes? Residents in our DDA programs are voluntarily placed through the DDA Residents go through a qualification process with DDA and are then referred to our Residents placed in our BRS programs are placed by their Washington state social worker and their region‚Äôs group care What does Steadfast Supported Living staff do? How CarBevy is Addressing Car Buyers" Pain Points and Reshaping their Car Buying Experience | CarBevy We are live in San Diego, CA with our beta We currently support Toyota, Ford, Kia, Hyundai and Get Notified when we add your brand or come to your How Carbevy Works About About us Contact us Blog Sign In Main menu November , by Joe Wirija How CarBevy is Addressing Car Buyers‚Äô Pain Points and Reshaping their Car Buying Experience How CarBevy is Addressing Car Buyers‚Äô Pain Points and Reshaping their Car Buying Experience November , by Joe Wirija A ‚Äúpain point‚Äù isn‚Äôt a medical term, but a business It‚Äôs defined as a specific problem that prospective customers of a business are experiencing a point that makes the process of using a particular service or commercial The world of automotive sales and driving are home to many such pain A report from a GfK market research identified no fewer than pain points for modern drivers, of which stem from experience and others connected to the car buying It is the latter that we want to explore in today‚Äôs Current Challenges Facing the EV Market During , even before the onset of the global pandemic, the car dealers was experiencing lengthy inventory A blog piece on pointed to US figures that showed vehicles sold in May had spent a lot longer on average sat on the dealer lot before sale than even when the world was dealing with the Great The average was days on the lot before finally being What does this suggest about the world of automotive sales? Even before we dive in to the detail, it‚Äôs telling us that customers in general remain dissatisfied with the overall experience and process of buying a new Below we study three of the biggest pain points in more detail and some possible solutions that car buyers could Pain Point 1: Car Buying process is and Complicated Solution: Aggregators that Connect Customers with Models --- CarBevy What time is used in the current car buying process? Think about it: first you spend a lot of time researching the cars you want, then you have to find local You need to pinpoint their locations and either drop in one day or make further telephone inquiries to find out if they have what you If they don‚Äôt, then you have to wait longer for them to get your dream model from their All of this is before you get to all the paperwork needed to actually purchase the things and drive it off the Automotive aggregators like are built to take the sting out of buying a Their goal is to cut down wasted time by connecting users with various dealership and, more importantly, showing them the items that they actually have in Using this platform, customers can connect directly with a dealer that has the exact car they want, ready to This greatly speeds up the process, and simplifies it, You don‚Äôt have to wade through the sales patter as you tell them what you want and they counter with something else they want to sell Pain Point 2: Haggling with the Dealer is Unpleasant Solution: Customers Name Their Price and Wait for the Dealers to Come to Them The days of hustling for bargains are firmly behind The modern consumer does not enjoy the process of bargaining, preferring the ‚Äúone-click purchase‚Äù culture created by online shopping experiences they engage with Younger buyers like to see a price, agree with it and take This is where platforms like once again have a role to CarBevy allows buyers to first name their The vast majority have done their online research in advance, and they know roughly how much the car should cost, and how much they are willing to This is then sent to multiple dealers, who will either take it or leave It‚Äôs a neat It‚Äôs good for dealers because they are connecting with a willing buyer who is even setting out a It‚Äôs also good for buyers because it‚Äôs very likely dealers will snap up these offers in order to stay competitive in a tough It‚Äôs Pain Point 3: Pricing is Steered by the Dealerships Solution: Put Some of This Power in the Hands of the Buyer It has always been the practice that buyers followed the prices set by The dealers, in turn, were usually following recommended retail rates from either their parent or from the going market rates plus reasonable profit for the The result of all this is a system where new car buyers are shut out of the pricing Online platforms often claim to be offering ‚Äúthe best price,‚Äù but is that true? Since they are in a partnership with the dealerships, it follows that their primary directive is to benefit their own company (and shareholders) and the This means prices will be set to achieve those goals, and not to genuinely save the buyer Allowing car buyers some purchase in the pricing arena ‚Äî as they do get on ‚Äî means that the market will start to work for the This should solve the pain point of prices being constantly out of our control as Modern Car Buyers are Motivated by the Experience Though many tend to think of Generations Y and Z as cynical who eschew commercialism and refuse to buy cars, they couldn‚Äôt be m

September Survived a PONS Ischemic Stroke I experienced my first stroke and spent days in the hospital with no use of my Wow, what a life changer and this was only the October Consistently Low Blood Pressure My blood pressure was constantly very low 62, making therapy challenging as I was always on the verge of passing December A Second Stroke I survived my second Stroke, a TIA and spent 8 days in the hospital before going home‚Ä¶ December Thankful for Life It was great to spend the Holidays with Bob and our wire hair fox terriers in a calm January Heat Lamp Acupuncture Therapy I explored acupuncture for my stroke rehab with needles in my hands and feet to help the healing January Physical and Occupational Therapies Outpatient therapy at Good Samaritan Hospital was critical for improved mobility and the therapists helped me stay They are a gift from February First Dinner Getting dressed and ready was exhausting and thankfully Bob helped with my hair, false eyelashes and shoes‚Ä¶ he was a champion! March Hyperbaric Oxygen Therapy (HBOT) The HBOT therapy was relaxing and I believe the oxygen treatment helped me It became part of my weekly regimen with three sessions a April A Wonderful Caregiver We hired a caregiver to help Bob and I with everything around the house scheduling therapies, doctor appointments, she helps me with home exercises and drives me She is amazing! May Acupressure Therapy Remaining limber was important, and I really wasn‚Äôt good at stretching, so I reached out for some acupressure massage and therapy which kept me July Short Outdoor Walks Mentally, I needed to feel like I was getting back into the real world, and while sidewalks and curbs were tricky to navigate, Bob and my caregiver kept me September Beach Therapy This was fun but hard, as I needed to navigate hotel steps, restaurants, crowds and a lot of mental I did it, but it was November A New Set of Challenges Bob had a business trip to London, and I was determined to go with Our caregiver came with us, and I took my wheelchair and My therapists helped me practice exercises to prepare me for getting out of cabs, getting on escalators, and a lot of travel tips that made it December Holidays by the Sea The town of Carmel is magical, so this was a special Holiday with just Bob and I and our two fox I focused

Ôªø They are neurotransmitters that bind to cannabinoid Cannabinoid receptors are found throughout the central nervous system and peripheral nervous Two primary cannabinoid receptors were identified in the early ‚Äôs, termed CB1 and While CB1 is found predominantly in the central nervous system and brain, CB2 is linked to immune system Endocannabinoids bind to, as well as activate, cannabinoid There are two main endocannabinoids: Anandamide (based on the Sanskrit word ‚Äúananda‚Äù meaning ‚Äúinner bliss‚Äù) and , or These two molecules are produced naturally by the cells in the Ôªø Ôªø WÔªøe now know the endocannabinoid system is involved in a wide variety of processes, including pain, memory, mood, appetite, stress, sleep, metabolism, immune function, and reproductive Endocannabinoids are arguably one of the most widespread and versatile signaling molecules known to Ôªø Effects of Cannabis on Immune Function CB2 mRNA levels are affected in , NK cells, monocytes, PMNs, T8 cells, T4 cells Cannabinoids inhibits the rise of cAMP in leukocytes They activate the pathway THC concentrations that modulate immune response are greater than the dosage for psychoactivity Ôªø It is not known whether Cannabinoids target cancer stem cells in poorly differentiated tumors differently from the differentiated tumors Ôªø We used two sets of oral (OSCSCs OSCCs) and pancreatic tumors (MP2 ) to address this question Ôªø Ôªø Little is known about cannabinoid effects on immune function even less in regards to NK Ôªø Conflicting results have been published previously: Cannabinoids can suppress the immune system of healthy individuals Cannabinoids can activate the immune system of patients The Effect of Cannabis on Cancer Cannabinoids Effect and Its Mechanism of Action Get in Touch!
